Uh, you're in the pilot program too?

07:36.500 --> 07:38.668
No no no, I'm deaf. But oral.

07:38.702 --> 07:40.203
- Come on.
- Okay.

07:45.342 --> 07:46.342
I'm Teo.

07:46.377 --> 07:47.476
Daphne.

07:49.312 --> 07:50.380
So when do I get the "thank you"?

07:50.414 --> 07:52.015
For what?

07:52.049 --> 07:54.067
Uh, for being switched at birth.

07:54.101 --> 07:58.204
I lead a life of confusion and turmoil,

07:58.238 --> 08:01.124
and you get a private studio session

08:01.158 --> 08:02.125
with The Flaming Lips.

08:02.159 --> 08:03.209
Okay, it's not The Flaming Lips;

08:03.260 --> 08:04.861
it's their producer.

08:04.895 --> 08:06.179
But thank you.

08:06.230 --> 08:09.132
Actually, it's not so bad for me.

08:13.937 --> 08:15.154
So what's your angle these days?

08:15.205 --> 08:17.156
All nose to the grindstone.

08:17.207 --> 08:18.927
I guess it's kinda like
when all else fails,

08:18.942 --> 08:20.043
read the directions.

08:20.077 --> 08:22.962
When all else fails, try to make it work.

08:22.997 --> 08:24.297
Wow, after 11 years,

08:24.331 --> 08:27.000
you finally decided to
stop fighting it here.

08:27.051 --> 08:28.251
Congratulations.

08:28.285 --> 08:29.335
Excuse me? Hello?

08:29.386 --> 08:31.254
You're not allowed to park here.

08:31.288 --> 08:32.337
Mario, what's... what do you mean?

08:32.389 --> 08:34.307
It's us... Toby and Bay.

08:34.341 --> 08:35.991
But I was told the car
can't be here anymore.

08:36.025 --> 08:37.010
As long as it's painted like that.

08:40.297 --> 08:41.931
What's wrong with how it's painted?

08:41.965 --> 08:43.982
Some kind of anti-graffiti mandate.

08:44.018 --> 08:45.968
Doesn't fit the Buckner image.

08:45.986 --> 08:50.940
So 16-year-olds driving
$60,000 cars is fine,

08:50.974 --> 08:53.309
but a couple of sea
creatures are offensive?

08:53.327 --> 08:55.161
Just move it.

08:57.031 --> 08:58.281
Park it around back please.

09:04.621 --> 09:06.111
You're building a house here?

09:06.424 --> 09:08.991
- On a golf course?
- Yeah.

09:09.026 --> 09:10.960
Isn't this John and Kathryn golf course?

09:10.994 --> 09:12.962
Really?

09:12.996 --> 09:14.230
I had no idea.

09:17.167 --> 09:20.136
And we are building here, not just me.

09:20.170 --> 09:21.304
Any style you want...

09:21.338 --> 09:23.072
modern, victorian... 

09:23.107 --> 09:24.871
Angelo, I'm not leaving Daphne, 

09:24.308 --> 09:26.275
and she's not leaving the Kennishes.

09:26.310 --> 09:28.277
And a year and a half from
now when she leaves the house?

09:28.312 --> 09:29.946
Come on, dream a little!

09:29.980 --> 09:32.949
We can have a pool. We
can have a tennis court.

09:32.983 --> 09:34.743
We can make a space for
your mom if you want.

09:36.186 --> 09:38.321
Okay. But, Gina,

09:38.355 --> 09:40.323
- this is your money.
- No, it's not.

09:40.357 --> 09:43.092
We're married! Your name
is on the deed to the land.

09:43.127 --> 09:45.228
That is for immigration reasons only.

09:47.931 --> 09:49.065
This is crazy.

09:49.099 --> 09:51.217
Here you are, stressing, juggling bills.

09:51.251 --> 09:52.251
I'm doing fine!

09:52.302 --> 09:54.937
If the switch hadn't happened,

09:54.972 --> 09:56.939
we would still be together.

09:56.974 --> 10:00.209
All these things... car, house...

10:00.244 --> 10:03.012
they don't make up for the time we lost.

10:03.046 --> 10:05.348
But if we get back together,

10:05.382 --> 10:07.383
and enjoy them together...

10:09.386 --> 10:11.988
then the money is doing something good.

10:14.191 --> 10:15.925
I did always want a greenhouse.

10:17.194 --> 10:20.763
Then I will build the
finest greenhouse in Kansas.

10:29.640 --> 10:31.707
I was just coming into
your homeroom to find you.

10:31.742 --> 10:33.643
Mr. Reynolds wants to see you.

10:33.677 --> 10:34.777
But I moved it already.

10:34.812 --> 10:36.712
He's expecting you.

10:47.407 --> 10:49.242
This is Teo Hanahan.

10:49.293 --> 10:52.028
He's here for the pilot program.

10:52.062 --> 10:53.929
He was wandering around lost.

10:53.947 --> 10:54.964
She'll take care of you.

10:54.998 --> 10:55.998
Thanks.

11:29.233 --> 11:30.199
Hi! Sorry.

11:30.234 --> 11:31.200
I moved it, everything's okay.

11:31.234 --> 11:33.069
Hi, Mr. Feldman.

11:33.103 --> 11:34.871
Bay. Sit down.

11:34.905 --> 11:36.772
We wanna talk to you.

11:42.713 --> 11:43.946
Is everything okay?

11:43.981 --> 11:46.616
You got a 94 on your French exam.

11:46.650 --> 11:48.451
I did?!

11:48.485 --> 11:49.752
That's high for you, isn't it?

11:49.786 --> 11:51.454
Uh, I... I guess.

11:51.488 --> 11:54.223
But I've been studying
really hard, obviously.

11:54.258 --> 11:57.059
The thing is Bonnie Saterfield got a 97.

11:57.094 --> 12:01.163
- Okay.
- Which is actually not that unusual.

12:01.198 --> 12:02.265
Uh-huh.

12:02.299 --> 12:03.332
And Mr. Feldman has made me aware

12:03.367 --> 12:05.301
that she was sitting

12:05.335 --> 12:07.103
right in front of you.

12:09.706 --> 12:11.941
You think I cheated?

12:11.975 --> 12:14.744
We're just trying to
figure out what's what here.

12:14.778 --> 12:16.545
I... I didn't cheat.

12:16.580 --> 12:17.713
My biological father is French,

12:17.748 --> 12:20.449
which Monsieur Feldman knows.

12:20.484 --> 12:21.684
We have a student honor board

12:21.718 --> 12:23.753
as, of course, you know.

12:23.787 --> 12:26.689
You've been encouraging me
to study more all semester,

12:26.723 --> 12:29.458
and when I do, you wanna put
me in front of an honor board?

12:29.493 --> 12:31.227
The honor board is made up of your peers.

12:31.261 --> 12:33.095
You'll be treated fairly.

12:34.214 --> 12:35.197
Thank you.

12:37.100 --> 12:38.234
If I was being treated fairly,

12:38.268 --> 12:40.069
I wouldn't have to go in
front of an honor board.

12:47.706 --> 12:49.691
I was so impressed with your book.

12:49.725 --> 12:51.492
Well, thank you.

12:51.510 --> 12:53.260
And your testimony

12:53.279 --> 12:54.595
in that case against the hospital?

12:54.613 --> 12:56.297
You kept your cool.

12:56.332 --> 12:58.549
But you were so articulate
and powerful in damning them.

12:58.601 --> 13:00.134
Oh, I don't know.

13:00.168 --> 13:02.186
It didn't seem to convince the jury.

13:02.237 --> 13:04.238
Oh, those things can be funny.

13:04.272 --> 13:06.124
Ivan's done enough of those cases to know

13:06.175 --> 13:08.376
you can't always tell which
way the wind's gonna blow.

13:08.410 --> 13:11.145
You've handled this whole thing
with such grace under fire.

13:11.180 --> 13:12.246
We've all been talking about it.

13:12.281 --> 13:14.916
Really?

13:14.950 --> 13:16.050
That's nice.

13:20.189 --> 13:21.122
Nice shot.

13:21.156 --> 13:22.857
I don't know.

13:22.891 --> 13:24.892
It must have been some
kind of chronic depression.

13:24.927 --> 13:26.594
Who are you talking about, honey?

13:26.629 --> 13:27.662
Frank Slade.

13:27.696 --> 13:28.713
Oh, that's so sad.

13:28.764 --> 13:29.831
We didn't even know he was sick.

13:29.865 --> 13:31.566
Neither did we.

13:31.600 --> 13:33.735
You must be scrambling to
find someone to fill his seat.

13:33.769 --> 13:36.270
Funny you should say that.

13:36.305 --> 13:38.339
You're gonna have a
special election, right?

13:38.374 --> 13:39.390
Three months from now.

13:39.425 --> 13:42.377
People seem pretty rocked by his death.

13:42.411 --> 13:44.278
